34:04.000 --> 34:08.000
I mean, basically since the actual age in 800 BCE and onward,

34:08.000 --> 34:10.000
we've had this two-world model.

34:10.000 --> 34:13.000
And now we're going through a radical re-embedding.

34:13.000 --> 34:16.000
And for a lot of people, that's caused a kind of nihilism.

34:16.000 --> 34:19.000
But one of the things I would throw out to you is that

34:19.000 --> 34:23.000
there's a possibility in an emerging cognitive science,

34:23.000 --> 34:25.000
and a cognitive science in which embodiment and embeddiment

34:25.000 --> 34:30.000
are becoming central for appropriating that re-embedding process

34:30.000 --> 34:35.000
as a way of discovering, rediscovering how we can be at home,

34:35.000 --> 34:37.000
fundamentally at home in the world,

34:37.000 --> 34:40.000
and how the earth and our bodies co-create that home

34:40.000 --> 34:42.000
in a way that, again, protects us from horror

34:42.000 --> 34:45.000
and allows us to flourish as cognitive agents.

34:45.000 --> 34:49.000
So you did something I think is lovely,

34:49.000 --> 34:52.000
and I don't think that it's people who aren't quite deeply educated can do,

34:52.000 --> 34:55.000
is you pushed the problem quite a bit farther back in time.

34:55.000 --> 34:57.000
So I want to one-up you on that.

34:57.000 --> 34:59.000
Okay.

